# 8. Physics update

This is the core function. In readable form:

```js
function updatePhysics() {
  // 1) Pairwise attraction between every pair of nodes
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      const dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      const dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;

      const force = config.attraction / (dist * dist);
      const fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      const fy = (dy / dist) * force;

      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2) Spring forces
  for (let i = 0; i < springs.length; i++) {
    const n1 = getNode(springs[i].a);
    const n2 = getNode(springs[i].b);
    if (!n1 || !n2) continue;

    const dx = n2.x - n1.x;
    const dy = n2.y - n1.y;
    const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;

    const stretch = dist - springs[i].rest;
    const force = (springs[i].k || config.springCoeff) * stretch;

    n1.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    n1.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    n2.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    n2.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3) Damping + weak drift toward center + integrate position
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.centerDrift;
    nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.centerDrift;

    nodes[i].vx *= config.amplification;
    nodes[i].vy *= config.amplification;

    nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
    nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
  }
}
```

## Important note
The “attraction” math as written causes motion along the vector between nodes. Depending on sign convention, it may behave more like attraction or repulsion relative to the update direction, but the intent is clearly “global inverse-square force” plus springs.

