# 9. Particle spawning

Readable version:

```js
function spawnStreamParticle() {
  if (streams.length >= config.streamLimit) return;

  const node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;

  streams.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI) * SQRT1_2
  });
}
```

So every few ticks it emits a particle from a random node in a random direction.

---

# 10. Particle update

Readable version:

```js
function updateStreams() {
  for (let i = streams.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = streams[i];

    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.age++;

    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      streams.splice(i, 1);
      continue;
    }

    p.vx *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
    p.vy *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
  }
}
```

This makes particles drift and slowly slow down until they expire.

